<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Badarg on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/badarg/</link><description>Recent content in Badarg on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/badarg/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>badarg Error in Erlang</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/erlang/erlang-badarg/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/erlang/erlang-badarg/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;badarg&lt;/code&gt; error is raised when a BIF (Built-In Function) or standard library function receives an argument that is not of the expected type or value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passing non-numeric value to arithmetic operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using non-atom where atom expected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong type to string or list operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid arguments to built-in functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure proper types:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-erlang" data-lang="erlang"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% WRONG
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; atom.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% CORRECT
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Validate input first:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>error: bad argument in call to X</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/erlang/badarg/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/erlang/badarg/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;badarg&lt;/code&gt; error in Erlang is raised when a BIF (Built-In Function) or standard library function receives an argument that is not of the expected type or value. This is one of the most common runtime errors in Erlang and typically indicates a type mismatch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passing a non-numeric value to arithmetic operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using a non-atom where an atom is expected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passing the wrong type to string or list operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing invalid arguments to built-in functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-erlang" data-lang="erlang"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% WRONG: Adding a number to an atom
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; atom. &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% error: bad argument in call to erlang:&amp;#39;+&amp;#39;/2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% CORRECT: Ensure proper types
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-erlang" data-lang="erlang"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% WRONG: Using list_to_atom on invalid input
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Atom &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; list_to_atom(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;123&lt;/span&gt;). &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% error: bad argument in call to list_to_atom/1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% CORRECT: Validate input first
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Input &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; is_list(Input) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; true &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; Atom &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; list_to_atom(Input);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; false &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {error, invalid_input}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-erlang" data-lang="erlang"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% Example 1: Wrong type to math function
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;X &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; math:&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sqrt&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;).
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% error: bad argument in call to math:sqrt/1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% Example 2: Invalid list operation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Y &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; lists:&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;nth&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;]).
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% error: bad argument in call to lists:nth/2 (index must be &amp;gt;= 1)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% Example 3: Wrong argument to iolist_to_binary
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Z &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; iolist_to_binary(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;).
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;%% error: bad argument in call to iolist_to_binary/1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-debug"&gt;How to Debug&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check the stack trace with &lt;code&gt;erlang:get_stacktrace()&lt;/code&gt; in try/catch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;io:format&lt;/code&gt; to print argument types before the failing call&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add type guards with &lt;code&gt;is_number/1&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;is_list/1&lt;/code&gt;, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use dialyzer for static type analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/erlang/badmatch"&gt;badmatch: error: no match of right hand side value&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>